. Kilmarnock also competed in the [[2003\u201304 Scottish Cup|Scottish Cup]] and the [[2003\u201304 Scottish League Cup|League Cup]].\n\n==Summary==\n\n===Season===\nKilmarnock finished tenth in the [[2003\u201304 Scottish Premier League|Scottish Premier League]] with 42 points.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.espn.in/football/table?season=2003&league=SCO.1 | title=2003/04 Scottish Premiership Table 2003-04 | publisher=[[ESPN FC]] | work=espnfc.com | accessdate=13 April 2020}}</ref> They reached the second round of the [[Scottish League Cup|League Cup]], losing to [[Brechin City F.C.|Brechin City]]<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/matchstats?gameId=123589 | title=Brechin City vs. Kilmarnock | publisher=[[ESPN]] | work=espnfc.com | date=23 September 2003 | accessdate=12 April 2020}}</ref> and the fourth round of the [[Scottish Cup]], losing to [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/matchstats?gameId=137306 | title=Kilmarnock vs. Rangers | publisher=[[ESPN]] | work=espnfc.com | date=8 February 2004 | accessdate=13 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Results and fixtures==\n{{legend2|#ccffcc|Win|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#ffffcc|Draw|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#ffcccc|Loss|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#cccccc|Postponed|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n\n===Scottish Premier League===\n{{Main article|2003\u201304 Scottish Premier League}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:100%; text-align:center\"\n!Match!!Date!!Opponent!!Venue!!Result!!Attendance!!Scorers\n|-style=\"background: #FFCCCC;\"\n|1||9 August 2003||[[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]]||A||0\u20134||49,108||\n|-style=\"background: #CCFFCC;\"\n|2||16 August 2003||[[Partick Thistle F.C.|Partick Thistle]]||H||2\u20131||6,778||[[Martin Hardie|Hardie]] 46\u2019 [[Kris Boyd|Boyd]] 60\u2019\n|-style=\"background: #FFCCCC;\"\n|3||23 August 2003||[[Motherwell F.C.|Motherwell]]||A||1\u20132||5,087||[[Fr\u00e9d\u00e9ric Dindeleux|Dindeleux]] 76\u201