ocities.ws/aidanjburns/six2.html Six Two (6x,2x)(2x,6x)]\", ''Aidan's Juggling Page''. Accessed: November 3, 2016.</ref> || 4 || 2 || A\n|-\n| {{right|(6x,4)(4,2x)(4,4)(4,6x)(2x,4)(4,4)}} || Tennis<ref>\"[http://geocities.ws/aidanjburns/stennis.html Synchronous Four Ball Tennis]\", ''Aidan's Juggling Page''. Accessed: November 3, 2016.</ref> || 4 || 6 || A\n|-\n| {{right|(6x,4)(4,2x)(4,6x)(2x,4)}} || Synchronous 534<!--see [[:File:Siteswap 4b (6x,4)(4,2x)(4,6x)(2x,4).gif]]--><ref>\"[http://geocities.ws/aidanjburns/s534.html 'Synchronous 534' (6x,4)(4,2x)(4,6x)(2x,4)]\", ''Aidan's Juggling Page''. Accessed: November 3, 2016.</ref> || 4 || 4 || A\n|-\n| {{right|(6x,4)(4,6x)}} || (6x,4)(4,6x)<ref name=\"Beevers6\"/> || 5 || 2 || A\n|-\n| {{right|(6x,4x)}} || Half shower<ref name=\"Phillips\"/> || 5 || 1 || S\n|-\n| {{right|(6x,6x)(2x,2x)}} || (6x,6x)(2x,2x)<ref name=\"Jugglinglab\"/> || 4 || 2 || A\n|-\n| {{right|(8,2x)(4,2x)(2x,8)(2x,4)}} || Dan Bennett's box<ref name=\"Orgfaq\"/> || 4 || 4 || A\n|}\n<!--|-\n| {{right|###}} || NAME || # || P || SYMMETRY-->\n\n==Passing==\n<!--[[Passing (juggling)#Passing patterns]] links directly to this section.-->\n{{Main|Passing (juggling)}}\n{{hidden|1=Animations|ta1=right|multiline=y|2={{multiple image\n | align = \n | direction = vertical\n | width = 110\n | image1 = Passing 3jugglers 9balls Feeding 2-4-4beats top.gif\n | caption1 = <nowiki><3p2|3p1|3><3|3|3><3p3|3|3p1><3|3|3></nowiki>\n | image2 = Passing 4jugglers 12balls N-shape 4-2-2-4beats top.gif\n | caption2 = <nowiki><3|3p3|3p2|3><3|3|3|3><3p2|3p1|3p4|3p3><3|3|3|3></nowiki>\n | image4 = Classic 4beats passing 2juggler 6balls side.gif\n | caption4 = Four-count\n}}}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:100%;text-align:center;\"\n|+ Juggling patterns by siteswap\n! Siteswap || Name || Props || Period || Symmetry<br/> (S/A) || Timing<br/> (S/A)\n|-\n| {{right|<nowiki><3p|3p></nowiki>}} || One-count<ref name=\"Jugglinglab\"/> || 6 || 1 || S || A\n|-\n| {{right|<nowiki><3p3|3p3></nowiki> <br/>or <nowiki><33p|33p></nowiki>}} || Two-count<ref name=\"Jugglinglab\"/> || 6 || 2 || A || A\n|-\n| {{right|<nowiki><3p33|3p33></nowiki>}} || Three-count || 6 || 3 || S || A\n|-\n| {{right|<nowiki><3p333|3p333></nowiki>}} || Four-count || 6 || 4 || A || A\n|-\n| {{right|<nowiki><3p33333|3p33333></nowiki>}} || Six-count<ref>Besmehn, Bobby (1994). ''Juggling Step-by-Step'', p.65. \"Use four balls of one color and two of another color...every time an odd-colored ball reaches your right hand, pass it.\" Sterling. {{ISBN|0-8069-0815-7}}</ref><ref>Cassidy, John and Rimbeaux, B.C. (1988). ''Juggling for the Complete Klutz'', p.38. \"It helps...if one of you counts out loud every time a toss leaves your right hand[s]...On a pre-arranged number, say three [six beats], instead of tossing across to your own left hand, throw your bag...over to your friend's left hand.\" Klutz Press. Third edition. {{ISBN|0-932592-00-7}}</ref> || 6 || 6 || S || A\n|-\n| {{right|<nowiki><5p333><335p3></nowiki>}} || Simplest 4 count 7 prop<ref>Beever (2001), p.43.</ref> || 7 || 4 || A || A\n|}\n\n==Ladder diagrams==\n{{Gallery\n|title=\n|width=150 | height=50 | lines=2\n|align=center\n|File:Juggling - 3-ball (441) ladder diagram.svg |\n alt1=\n |Half-box: 441\n|File:Juggling - 3-ball (53145305520) ladder diagram.svg |\n alt2=\n |53145305520\n|File:Juggling - 3-ball box (4,2x)(2x,4) ladder diagram.svg |\n alt3=\n |Box: (4,2x)(2x,4)\n|File:Juggling - 3-ball Burke's barrage (423) ladder diagram.svg |\n alt4=\n |Burke's barrage: 423\n|File:Juggling - 3-ball cascade (3) ladder diagram.svg |\n alt5=\n |Cascade: 3\n|File:Juggling - 3-ball columns (nonalternating) ladder diagram.svg |\n alt6=\n |Columns: (4,4)(4,0)\n|File:Juggling - 3-ball columns alternating (4,4)(4x,0) ladder diagram.svg |\n alt7=\n |Columns, alternating: (4,4)(4x,0)\n|File:Juggling - 3-ball Rubenstein's revenge (52233) ladder diagram.svg |\n alt8=\n |Rubenstein's revenge: 52233\n|File:Juggling - 3-ball 